  <compounddef id="group__graph__module" kind="group">
    <compoundname>graph_module</compoundname>
    <title>Graph Module</title>
    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classGraph" kindref="compound">Graph</ref> construction and manipulation. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<sect1 id="group__graph__module_1graph_overview">
<title>Overview</title>
<para>The <ref refid="classGraph" kindref="compound">Graph</ref> module provides the <ref refid="classgraph__template" kindref="compound">graph_template</ref> class for constructing graph representations from physics events.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__graph__module_1graph_construction">
<title>Graph Construction</title>
<para>To create a graph:</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Subclass <ref refid="classgraph__template" kindref="compound">graph_template</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>In <computeroutput>CompileEvent()</computeroutput>, define which particles become nodes</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Define the edge topology using <computeroutput>define_topology()</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Add features using <computeroutput>add_node_data_feature()</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>add_edge_data_feature()</computeroutput>, etc.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__graph__module_1graph_features_mod">
<title>Feature Types</title>
<para>The graph template supports:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold><ref refid="classNode" kindref="compound">Node</ref> Data Features</bold> (D-*): Input features for nodes</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold><ref refid="classNode" kindref="compound">Node</ref> Truth Features</bold> (T-*): Target labels for nodes</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold><ref refid="classEdge" kindref="compound">Edge</ref> Data Features</bold> (D-*): Input features for edges</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold><ref refid="classEdge" kindref="compound">Edge</ref> Truth Features</bold> (T-*): Target labels for edges</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold><ref refid="classGraph" kindref="compound">Graph</ref> Data Features</bold> (D-*): Input features for entire graph</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold><ref refid="classGraph" kindref="compound">Graph</ref> Truth Features</bold> (T-*): Target labels for graph</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classgraph__template" kindref="compound">graph_template</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="structgraph__t" kindref="compound">graph_t</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
  </compounddef>
